---
source: crates/vize/src/cli.rs
expression: "command_help(\"build\")"
---
Compile Vue SFC files (default command)

Usage: build [OPTIONS] [PATTERNS]...

Arguments:
  [PATTERNS]...
          Glob pattern(s) to match .vue files (default: ./**/*.vue)

          [default: ./**/*.vue]

Options:
  -o, --output <OUTPUT>
          Output directory (default: ./dist)

          [default: ./dist]

  -c, --config <CONFIG>
          Config file path (accepted for npm CLI compatibility)

      --no-config
          Do not load a config file

  -f, --format <FORMAT>
          Output format

          Possible values:
          - js:    Output compiled JavaScript
          - json:  Output JSON with code and metadata
          - stats: Only show statistics (no output)

          [default: js]

      --ssr
          Enable SSR mode

      --vapor
          Enable Vapor mode

      --custom-renderer
          Target a custom renderer instead of DOM runtime helpers

      --vue-parser-quirks
          Enable Vue parser quirk compatibility for known edge cases

      --script-ext <SCRIPT_EXT>
          Script extension handling: 'preserve' keeps original extension (.ts/.tsx/.jsx), 'downcompile' converts to .js

          Possible values:
          - preserve:    Preserve original script language extension (.ts -> .ts, .tsx -> .tsx, .jsx -> .jsx)
          - downcompile: Downcompile all scripts to JavaScript (.ts -> .js, .tsx -> .js, .jsx -> .js)

          [default: downcompile]

  -j, --threads <THREADS>
          Number of threads (default: number of CPUs)

      --profile
          Show timing profile breakdown

      --slow-threshold <SLOW_THRESHOLD>
          Slow file threshold in milliseconds (default: 100)

          [default: 100]

      --continue-on-error
          Continue on errors (collect all errors and show at end)

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')
